## Superseded from enable-mypy-check-untyped-defs

```yaml
name: enable-mypy-check-untyped-defs
description: Enable mypy --check-untyped-defs for full Python body type coverage and fix surfaced errors.
category: ci-cd
date: 2026-03-07
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Enable mypy `--check-untyped-defs` for full Python body type coverage. Verified on
ProjectOdyssey issue #3370, PR #4036.

Key findings:
- Always run `pixi run mypy <dir>/ --check-untyped-defs` MANUALLY before committing config changes.
- `defaultdict` in untyped bodies needs explicit `defaultdict[str, int]` annotation.
- Empty lists need explicit `list[str] = []` annotation.
- Pillow 10+ deprecated module-level aliases: use `Image.Resampling.LANCZOS` not `Image.LANCZOS`;
  `Image.Transpose.TRANSPOSE` not `Image.TRANSPOSE`.
- Both `pyproject.toml` and `.pre-commit-config.yaml` hook args must be updated.

Triage command: `pixi run mypy <source-dir>/ --check-untyped-defs --exclude <excluded-dir>/`

pyproject.toml reference:
```toml
[tool.mypy]
disallow_untyped_defs = true
check_untyped_defs = true
```

Failed attempts: None — triage-first approach worked without surprises.

