## Superseded from fix-placeholder-code-ci

```yaml
name: fix-placeholder-code-ci
description: Fix CI failures caused by partially commented placeholder code and dtype migration assertion mismatches
category: testing
date: 2025-12-31
version: 1.0.0
```

Fix CI failures from partially commented placeholder code and dtype migration assertion
mismatches. ProjectOdyssey PR #3017 — 58 CI checks passing.

Key findings:
- When commenting out a function call, comment out ALL code that uses its return value.
- After type migration (aliased → native), update all test assertions to match the new native type.
- After any rebase, always run pre-commit locally before pushing — never wait for CI with conflicts.
- Merge conflicts can leave orphaned `Returns:` docstring lines causing parse errors.
- Fix: add `_ = a` to suppress unused variable warnings from placeholder removal.

Triage commands:
```bash
gh run view <run_id> --repo <owner>/<repo> --log-failed 2>&1 | head -200
gh run view <run_id> --repo <owner>/<repo> --log-failed 2>&1 | grep -A 50 "error:\|FAILED"
```

