## Superseded from markdownlint-md024-siblings-only-for-changelogs

```yaml
name: markdownlint-md024-siblings-only-for-changelogs
description: "Fix markdownlint MD024/no-duplicate-heading false positives on Keep-a-Changelog CHANGELOG.md files by setting siblings_only: true."
category: tooling
date: 2026-05-17
version: "1.0.0"
user-invocable: false
verification: verified-ci
tags: [markdownlint, MD024, changelog, keep-a-changelog, duplicate-heading, siblings_only]
```

Stop MD024 false positives on Keep-a-Changelog CHANGELOG.md without renaming headings or
disabling the rule globally. Verified on ProjectAgamemnon PR #404 (2026-05-17) — 14 violations
to 0 violations after a 3-line config change; CHANGELOG.md unchanged.

Config fix:
```yaml
# .markdownlint.yaml
MD024:
  siblings_only: true
```

Failed attempts:
1. Renaming headings `### Added in 0.2.0` — breaks release-drafter and auto-changelog tooling
   that expects literal `### Added` / `### Fixed`. Convention is load-bearing for tooling.
2. `MD024: false` globally — too permissive, real same-parent duplicates silently pass.
3. Inline `<!-- markdownlint-disable MD024 -->` per release block — verbose, must be added for
   every new release, easy to forget, disables real duplicate detection within each block.

