## Superseded from narrow-mypy-override-subset

```yaml
name: narrow-mypy-override-subset
description: Narrow a broad mypy module glob override to an explicit list when a subset of subdirs is fully annotated.
category: testing
date: 2026-03-02
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Narrow a broad `tests.unit.*` mypy override glob to an explicit list when one subdir is fully
annotated. ProjectScylla PR #1316, issue #1287.

Key insight: The annotation task may already be complete. Always triage before touching files:
```bash
pixi run mypy tests/unit/<subdir>/ --disallow-untyped-defs
# "Success: no issues found" → skip test file edits, only change pyproject.toml
```

In the reference session, `tests/unit/scripts/` (9 files, 192 tests) had zero mypy errors from
the start. Only `pyproject.toml` changed: broad `tests.unit.*` glob → 14-entry explicit list.

Find remaining subdirs needing suppression:
```bash
pixi run mypy tests/unit/ --disallow-untyped-defs --no-error-summary 2>&1 \
  | grep "error:" | sed 's|tests/unit/||;s|/.*||' | sort -u
```

Note: mypy `[[tool.mypy.overrides]]` accepts a `module` array as of mypy 0.930+.

Failed attempts: None — direct approach worked.

