## Superseded from testing-regression-guard-syntax-vs-property-assertion

```yaml
name: testing-regression-guard-syntax-vs-property-assertion
description: "Refactor regression-guard tests that assert on the exact literal text of a suppression mechanism to instead assert the underlying property."
category: testing
date: 2026-05-11
version: "1.0.0"
user-invocable: false
verification: verified-ci
tags: [meta-tests, regression-guard, syntax-pinning, property-assertion, ecosystem-sweep]
```

Refactor regression-guard tests from syntax-pinning to property assertions before ecosystem sweeps.
Verified on ProjectScylla PR #1968 and ProjectOdyssey PR #5385 / #5387.

Pre-sweep grep:
```bash
grep -rn "continue-on-error\|or-true\|::warning::" tests/ .github/ \
  --include="*.py" --include="*.sh" --include="*.bats" --include="*.yml" --include="*.yaml"
```

Fix in a predecessor PR before the sweep, or every sweep PR's CI will fail on meta-test brittleness.

Failed attempts:
1. Running sweep first, fixing meta-tests after CI broke — reviewers confused real regressions
   with test brittleness; CI ran twice per PR.
2. Replacing pinned literal with new mechanism's literal — broke again on the next sweep iteration.
3. Runtime property check via `gh workflow run` — too slow for pre-merge fast-feedback.
4. `re.search()` over raw workflow file text — false positives from other steps' commented code.
5. Smoke-test error message containing `::warning::` triggered `forbid-advisory-warnings` hook
   on the test file itself. Fix: exclude via `exclude:` in `.pre-commit-config.yaml`.

